@index "CanDo_LexiconIndex"

@node "CanDo_Flow Control_Index" "Flow Control Commands, Functions and Variables"
@toc "CanDo_LexiconMain"
@{fg highlight}Available Topics...@{fg text}

  Variable @{" =Arg1                          " link "CanDo_Arg1"}
  Variable @{" =ArgCount                      " link "CanDo_ArgCount"}
  Command  @{" Do                             " link "CanDo_Do"}
  Command  @{" Else                           " link "CanDo_Else"}
  Command  @{" ElseIf                         " link "CanDo_ElseIf"}
  Command  @{" EndIf                          " link "CanDo_EndIf"}
  Command  @{" EndLoop                        " link "CanDo_EndLoop"}
  Command  @{" ExitLoop                       " link "CanDo_ExitLoop"}
  Command  @{" ExitScript                     " link "CanDo_ExitScript"}
  Command  @{" If                             " link "CanDo_If"}
  Command  @{" Loop                           " link "CanDo_Loop"}
  Command  @{" Quit                           " link "CanDo_Quit"}
  Command  @{" StopScript                     " link "CanDo_StopScript"}
  Command  @{" Until                          " link "CanDo_Until"}
  Command  @{" While                          " link "CanDo_While"}

@endnode

@node "CanDo_arg1" "Let {Argument}=Arg1"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  Let {Argument}=Arg1

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  This returns one of the arguments passed to this script.  Up to ten
arguments may be passed to a script, Arg1 through Arg10.
  
  SEE ALSO: @{" ArgCount " link "CanDo_ArgCount"}.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_argcount" "Let {Integer}=ArgCount"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  Let {Integer}=ArgCount

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  This returns the number of arguments that were passed to this script.
This could be anything from Zero(0) to Ten(10).
  
  SEE ALSO: @{" Arg1 " link "CanDo_Arg1"}.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_do" "Do {RoutineName} [,{Arg1} [,up to ten arguments]]"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  Do {RoutineName} [,{Arg1} [,up to ten arguments]]

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

Performs the routine created using the Routine Object.  The routine can use
the optional Arguments as incoming data.  See the manual for a full
description of this command.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_else" "Else"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  Else

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Used with the @{" If " link "CanDo_If"} command.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_elseif" "ElseIf {Logical}"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  ElseIf {Logical}

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Used with the @{" If " link "CanDo_If"} command.  This allows you to have multiple exclusive
true code blocks.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_endif" "EndIf"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  EndIf

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Used with the @{" If " link "CanDo_If"} command.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_endloop" "EndLoop"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  EndLoop

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Can be used to mark the end of a looping code block.  This end marker
will always start the block of code over again.

   @{" Loop " link "CanDo_Loop"}
     ..code..
   EndLoop

@endnode

@node "CanDo_exitloop" "ExitLoop"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  ExitLoop

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  This will abort a loop block and can only be used within a loop block.
  
  SEE ALSO: @{" Loop " link "CanDo_Loop"}, @{" While " link "CanDo_While"} and @{" Until " link "CanDo_Until"}.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_exitscript" "ExitScript"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  ExitScript

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  This will abort the current script executing.  If the script was called
from another script then that script will take over again.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_if" "If {Logical}"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  If {Logical}

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  This is used for condition flow control.

    If {Logical}
      ..code executed if {Logical} is true..
    @{" Else " link "CanDo_Else"}
      ..code executed if {Logical} is false..
    @{" EndIf " link "CanDo_EndIf"}

@endnode

@node "CanDo_loop" "Loop"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  Loop

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Can be used to mark the start of a looping code block.  This allows for
repeating blocks of code.

   Loop
     ..code..
   @{" EndLoop " link "CanDo_EndLoop"}

@endnode

@node "CanDo_quit" "Quit"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  Quit

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Allows the user to exit the presently running Deck.  If running under
CanDo this command will not work.  However, it will work if running as a
separate application.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_stopscript" "StopScript"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  StopScript

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Similar to @{" ExitScript " link "CanDo_ExitScript"}.  However, if it is performed from a Routine,
execution will not continue in the calling script.

@endnode

@node "CanDo_until" "Until {Logical}"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  Until {Logical}

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Can be used to mark the end of a looping code block.  This end marker
will loopback only if the logical proves false.

   @{" Loop " link "CanDo_Loop"}
     ..code..
   Until TheLine=Nothing

@endnode

@node "CanDo_while" "While {Logical}"
@toc "CanDo_Flow Control_Index"
@{fg highlight}Command...@{fg text}

  While {Logical}

@{fg highlight}Description...@{fg text}

  Can be used to mark the start of a looping code block.  This allows for
conditional repeating blocks of code.

   While Test<>15
     ..code..
   @{" EndLoop " link "CanDo_EndLoop"}

@endnode

